{
    "name": "cpig-kin-01-fork-diagram",
    "workload": "rhino",
    "description": "kin-01 Fork Diagram \u2014 load the leading-link front-fork mechanism (4 bodies, 4 revolutes, 1 coil-over spring), validate to 1 DOF planar / 1 loop \"fourbar\" / 0 errors, and preview the skeletal four-bar diagram in the viewport.",
    "runMode": "shared",
    "setup": {
        "file": "fixtures/cpig_slop_loader.gh",
        "viewport": {
            "projection": "Perspective",
            "displayMode": "Shaded",
            "width": 800,
            "height": 600
        },
        "commands": [],
        "vlm": {
            "provider": "ollama",
            "model": "gemma4:e2b"
        },
        "vlmDescription": "A four-bar linkage front-fork skeleton drawn in line-art: a vertical ground column on the left with two ground pivots, two parallel horizontal links extending to the right to a wheel-carrier link, and a diagonal coil-spring (visible zig-zag pattern) between the top of the column and the upper link. Each pivot shows a small orange circle (revolute glyph). At every named frame a small red/green/blue axis triad is visible. Text labels mark the bodies and joints."
    },
